HEADWORD: Sulliage
<hw>Sul"li*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Sullage</er>, <er>Suillage</er>, or <er>Sully</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Foulness; filth.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though we wipe away with never so much care the dirt thrown at us,
there will be left some <qex>sulliage</qex> behind.</q> <rj><qau>Gov. of
Tongue.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sully</ent>⟦br⟧
